FIX — Switch default image model to Seedream 4.5 for cost efficiency

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
CONTEXT
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Real measured cost per product on google/gemini-3.1-flash-image is
~$0.30 (3 images at 1K @ $0.0672 + 1 image at 2K @ $0.1008), because
that model bills per image-token and does not scale flat with
resolution. ByteDance's Seedream 4.5 bills at a flat rate regardless
of resolution, making 2K delivery images no more expensive than 1K
listing images. Switch the default model.

Model slug to use: "bytedance-seed/seedream-4.5" — note the slug is
"bytedance-seed", NOT "bytedance". Getting this wrong will 400.

Note: OpenRouter's own materials disagree with each other on the
exact per-image price — the model's public page states $0.04/image,
but a cached docs example shows cost_usd: 0.05 for the same model.
Do not trust either figure — get the real number from a live response
per step 3 below.

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
STEP 1 — Confirm this model's actual accepted parameters first
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Fetch https://openrouter.ai/api/v1/images/models/bytedance-seed/seedream-4.5/endpoints
before changing any code. Confirm:
  - It accepts "resolution" (enum: 1K/2K/4K per public docs) and
    "aspect_ratio" — confirm the exact accepted aspect_ratio values,
    since Seedream reportedly supports 18 aspect ratios but the
    precise list needs verifying against this specific endpoint, not
    assumed from the general marketing page.
  - Confirm it does NOT require any parameter your current
    OpenRouterImageProvider isn't already sending (e.g. check if
    "n" or "seed" are required vs optional — per the docs these
    appear optional with sensible defaults).

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
STEP 2 — Change the default model setting
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

In config/settings.py, find:
    OPENROUTER_IMAGE_MODEL: str = "google/gemini-3.1-flash-image"

Replace with:
    OPENROUTER_IMAGE_MODEL: str = "bytedance-seed/seedream-4.5"

Do NOT change anything in openrouter_image_provider.py itself unless
step 1's endpoint check reveals it sends a parameter this model
doesn't accept (in which case, fix only that specific mismatch — the
provider is supposed to already be model-agnostic per how it was
built).

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
STEP 3 — Re-run the real verification test with the new model
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Re-run scripts/test_openrouter_image_provider.py as-is (it already
makes real 1:1/1K and 1:1/2K calls and decodes real dimensions via
Pillow, and will now hit Seedream instead of Gemini since it reads
settings.OPENROUTER_IMAGE_MODEL). Confirm:
  - Real dimensions returned for 1:1 @ 1K and 1:1 @ 2K (may differ
    from Gemini's 1024×1024/2048×2048 — don't assume they match).
  - Real actual cost per call from the response's usage/cost field —
    this is the authoritative number, overriding both conflicting
    cached prices mentioned in CONTEXT above.
  - If dimensions differ from Gemini's, check whether
    image_validation_service.py's minimum thresholds (1000×1000) are
    still satisfied — update only if they're not.

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
STEP 4 — Update the per-product cost estimate
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Using the real confirmed per-call cost from step 3, recalculate:
  per-product cost = (2 listing images + 1 Pinterest image, all 1K)
                    + (1 delivery image, 2K)
using Seedream's real confirmed price, not the $0.04/$0.05 guesses
from CONTEXT. Since Seedream is flat-rate, this should just be
4 × (real confirmed per-image price).

